    • useVanillaBlockBreaking

      default boolean useVanillaBlockBreaking()
      This method determines how to treat this Block when it is broken. If true is returned then it will be treated as a vanilla Block. If false is returned then Slimefun will treat it as a Block that is the placed down version of a SlimefunItem. It returns false by default. This was previously represented by the HandledBlock class.
      Returns:
      Whether to use the vanilla block breaking behaviour
